  "title": "Deploying and Using Harbor in Kubernetes",
  "type": "lab",
  "description": "This experiment guides the user through the deployment of Harbor in a Kubernetes cluster, which is a registry server for storing and distributing Docker images. The process includes adding the official Harbor Helm Chart repository, downloading the Charts locally, creating a namespace and custom configuration for the Harbor deployment, and finally installing Harbor using the Helm command. Once Harbor is deployed, the user can log in, create a dev user for pushing and downloading images, and use Harbor for storing and managing their Docker images. The experiment requires familiarity with Kubernetes, Helm, Docker, and Dockerfile syntax.",
